						<summary>

						<p>This is an inscription of <hi rend="bold">Jagadēkamalladēva</hi> who had his capital at <hi rend="bold">[Poṭṭaḷakeṟe].</hi> Neither the date nor the contents of the record are available as the stone is broken off in the middle. On palaeographical grounds, the record may be assigned to Jagadēkamalla Jayasiṁha II.</p>						

						</summary>
